As part of this strategy, Cuomo has hired the consultant firm McKinsey & Company to help him develop the plan.
But what should be making people suspicious is the firm’s long, very close ties to the Chinese Communist Party.
But the BRI was yet another far-reaching effort to expand China’s tendrils into governments and private businesses around the globe, locking down their control of the global supply chain even further.
Their clients in these efforts included IBM and General Motors, both of which became famous for outsourcing jobs and supply chain sources.
They would be risking drawing the anger of one of their largest cash cows and closest business partners, the CCP.